{
  "texts": [
    "Their baseline is the LangID classifier [Lui and Baldwin 2012] where dialects are treated as individual languages.",
    "They experiment with classifiers using features such as n-grams and POS-n-grams.",
    "This includes a distribution over function words and those in a vocabulary, akin to a clustering algorithm.",
    "Simaki et al. [2017] use linguistic, POS-tag-based and lexicon-based features.",
    "Deep learning-based Approaches.Deep learning-based approaches for dialect classification span three alternatives: train embeddings to reflect dialectal variations, use end-to-end LLMs, or predict dialect as a result of inference over dialect features."
  ]
}